dev-guide-archetype.title: Start Developing
dev-guide-archetype.description: In this tutorial we explain how you can use the Maven archetypes to develop your own StreamPipes processors and sinks.

dev-guide-configuration.title: Configuration
dev-guide-configuration.description: On this page we explain how the StreamPipes configuration works.

dev-guide-development-environment.title: Development Environment
dev-guide-development-environment.description: In this section, we describe our recommended minimum setup for locally setting up a development instance of StreamPipes needed to develop, run and test new pipeline elements.

dev-guide-tutorial-processors.title: Tutorial: Data Processors
dev-guide-tutorial-processors.description: In this tutorial, we will add a new data processor using the Apache Flink wrapper.

dev-guide-tutorial-sinks.title: Tutorial: Data Sinks
dev-guide-tutorial-sinks.description: In this tutorial, we will add a new data sink using the standalone wrapper.

dev-guide-tutorial-sources.title: Tutorial: Data Sources
dev-guide-tutorial-sources.description: In this tutorial, we will add a new data source consisting of a single data stream. The source will be provided as a standalone component (i.e., the description will be accessible through an integrated web server).

user-guide-first-steps.title: First steps
user-guide-first-steps.description: In this section, you'll learn how to create and run pipelines in StreamPipes.
